      <hedline>
        <hl1>Dante at St. Andrews</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Harold A Seagall letter comments on July 24 article on David Duval's quadruple-bogy on final 17th hole of British Open</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>David Duval was paired with Tiger Woods on the final round of the British Open at the Old Course, when Duval had the misfortune of hitting his second shot into the bunker on the 17th hole (Sports pages, July 24). He took four shots to get out, for a quadruple-bogey.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>David Duval was paired with Tiger Woods on the final round of the British Open at the Old Course, when Duval had the misfortune of hitting his second shot into the bunker on the 17th hole (Sports pages, July 24). He took four shots to get out, for a quadruple-bogey.</p>
        <p>A small sign should be posted close to the bunker, quoting from Dante's ''Inferno'': ''Abandon all hope, ye who enter here.''</p>
        <p>HAROLD A. SEGALL  Harrison, N.Y., July 25, 2000</p>
      </block>
